  <h1 class="mb-4 text-center">Welcome to Haba na Haba</h1>

  <section class="mb-4">
    <p>At <strong>Haba na Haba</strong>, our mission is to empower individuals, households, and communities to access, utilize, and save surplus food resources effectively, efficiently, and sustainably. We believe in creating a world where food waste is minimized, and hunger is eradicated through innovative and community-driven solutions.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-4">
    <p>Food waste and hunger are two of the most pressing issues of our time. Despite the abundance of food produced globally, a significant portion goes to waste, while millions of people suffer from hunger. There is also a connection gap between those who have surplus food and those who need it, exacerbating the problem.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-4">
    <p>Our target audience encompasses individuals, households, and communities, as well as NGOs and other groups combating hunger, and waste points. We aim to educate and empower them to reduce food waste, share surplus food, and enhance their efforts in addressing hunger.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-4">
    <p>The goal of our solution is to ensure efficient and effective redistribution and saving of surplus food, improved nutritional access for all community members, and community empowerment through active participation in addressing food waste and hunger.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-4">
    <p>We measure our success through various criteria including increased access to nutritious food, improved health outcomes, reduction in food waste, increased food security, community engagement, economic empowerment, policy influence, client satisfaction, collaborative partnerships, and environmental impact.</p>
  </section>
